Comments.Message:
I found the problem. It appears that on line 714 of AccordionItem.cs, the ParentAccordion property is null when accessing via the designer, but not at run-time. I fixed this by simply adding:

if (ParentAccordion == null) return;

above line 714. HOWEVER, this is simply me working around it and getting on with life. This is by no means the real way of dealing with this issue or any sort of real solution. I wouldn't use this in production, just in case :P
